11/08/2010
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- A total of 21 suspected members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) were arrested during a police operation in Istanbul on Tuesday (August 10th). 
The arrests were conducted simultaneously in the districts of Sisli, Beyoglu and Kagithane. 
Local media reported the suspects were plotting an attack. 
(Yeni Safak - 11/08/10; CNN Turk - 10/08/10)
